<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Links & Info</title>
</head>
<body>
<p>IMPORTANT: MySQL must be running and the silex_blog_a9 database must be imported before the blog application will work!</p>
<p>All routes that deal with blog posts should be under /blog.  Here are the existing ones:
<ul>
    <li><a href="{{ path('findAllPosts') }}">{{ path('findAllPosts') }}</a> - list of all blog posts.</li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('findPost', {id: 1}) }}">{{ path('findPost', {id: 1}) }}</a> - view a specific post by its ID.</li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('newPost') }}">{{ path('newPost') }}</a> - form to create a new post.</li>
</ul>
<p>Added ones:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="{{ path('findByAuthorName', {author: 'David'}) }}">{{ path('findByAuthorName', {author: 'David'}) }}</a> - view a specific post by Author name.</li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('editPost', {id: 1}) }}">{{ path('editPost', {id: 1}) }}</a> - Edit a blog post by id</li>
    <p>delete post functionality is shown by viewing all posts</p>
    <li><a href="{{ path('addComment', {id: 3}) }}">{{ path('addComment', {id: 3}) }}</a> - Add a comment to a blog post.</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>All routes that deal with users should be under /user.  Here are the existing ones:
<ul>
    <li><a href="{{ path('userLogin') }}">{{ path('userLogin') }}</a> - the login form.</li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('userTest') }}">{{ path('userTest') }}</a> - test to see if a user is currently logged in.</li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('userShowRoles') }}">{{ path('userShowRoles') }}</a> - show the roles of a currently logged in user.</li>
    <li><a href="/user/logout">/user/logout</a> - log out a currently logged in user.</li>
    <li>/user/login_check - processes the login form input.</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>Existing usernames and passwords:</p>
<ul>
    <li>username - password - roles</li>
    <li>admin - foo - ROLE_ADMIN, ROLE_USER</li>
    <li>testuser - foo - ROLE_USER</li>
    <li>testuser2 - foo - ROLE_COMMENTER</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>